  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject scheduled for Direct Anterior unilateral total hip replacement

          -  Weight ≥ 50 and ≤125 kg

          -  Intact neurological exam

          -  Cognitively intact with ability to sign consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Renal insufficiency with creatinine &gt; 1.5 mg/dl

          -  Allergic to any of the following : Ropivacaine, Epinephrine, Ketorolac, Morphine
             sulfate, NSAIDs, Tylenol, Neurontin, Morphine, Oxycodone or Dilaudid.

          -  Subject taking regular narcotic medications prior to surgery (20mg/day Morphine
             equivalents for &gt;7days)

          -  Subject with prior open hip surgery who received regional anesthesia or periarticular
             injection for post op pain management.

          -  Subject with contraindication for spinal anesthesia
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
